<title>USA: Avondale navy contract reaffirmed by GAO.</title>
<headline>Avondale navy contract reaffirmed by GAO.</headline>
<dateline>NEW ORLEANS 1997-04-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Avondale Industries Inc said Monday the General Accounting Office has denied a protest filed by a rival for a $641 million contract to build an LPD-17 amphibious ship for the U.S. Navy.</p>
<p>Avondale said the Navy followed the GAO decision and has canceled its previously issued stop work order. &quot;As a consequence, the company will resume work immediately under the contract,&quot; Avondale said in a release.  </p>
<p>A subsidiary of Litton Industries filed the protest in December after an alliance headed by Avondale won the contract. The contract is worth as much as $1.5 billion because it includes options to build two more LPD-17 ships.</p>
<p>The Avondale alliance includes General Dynamics Corp's Bath Iron Works Corp, Hughes Electronics Corp's Hughes Aircraft Co and Intergraph Corp.</p>
